v. 盘绕；把…做成花环 【英】 v. 盘绕(coil about something)；把…做成花环(to shape into a wreath) 【记】 wreath(花环)+e 【例】 Mist wreathed the hilltops. v. 使缠绕或编织成环 【记】wreath(n 花环), e: 编织w = we, rea = ready, the神: 我们为神准备的东西－花环－编织 【记】音：人死，给死人wraith准备的；音：无 + breathe 呼吸，无呼吸→死→送花圈 wreathe (v.)  1520s (transitive), a back-formation from wrethen, Middle English past participle of writhe. Intransitive sense from 1580s. Related: Wreathed; wreathing.
